# Repository-local docs standards

These rules apply to the docs site in `docs/`.

## Scope

- Document this repository's Mattermost product behavior and administration workflows.
- Use the current source tree as the authority. Do not copy from public Mattermost docs.
- Keep developer architecture notes out of this site unless they directly explain admin-visible behavior.
- If behavior depends on license, plugin installation, or configuration, say so.

## Structure

- Product pages live under `docs/product/`.
- Administration pages live under `docs/admin/`.
- Integration pages live under `docs/integrations/`.
- Navigation lives in `docs/.vitepress/config.mts`; add new pages to the sidebar when they should be discoverable.

## Writing style

- Use sentence case headings.
- Prefer short paragraphs and task-oriented bullets.
- Name the setting, feature, role, or workflow directly.
- Avoid marketing language and broad claims that are not visible in the source.
- Use inline code for config keys, commands, endpoints, file paths, plugin IDs, and role IDs.

## Source discipline

- Before editing docs, inspect the relevant source files and existing docs page.
- For System Console behavior, start with `webapp/channels/src/components/admin_console/admin_definition.tsx`.
- For defaults and config behavior, inspect `server/public/model/config.go`.
- For roles and permissions, inspect `server/public/model/role.go` and `server/public/model/permission.go`.
- For integrations, inspect `webapp/channels/src/components/integrations/` and server handlers such as `server/channels/web/webhook.go`.
